The resolution for a Green New Deal (GND) made a splash in Washington earlier this year.
PPP’s analysis focuses on the United Nations’ Green Climate Fund (GCF), an international financial organ created in 2010 through the U.N. climate talks.
And it would build on years of progress in government-led stimulus of green energy development.
But a global Green New Deal will require a big upfront investment before it starts paying for itself.
And it can start by making a Green New Deal with the rest of the world.